ANYWAY. Point is, I love these characters, I love their friendship, I'm obsessed with them, I think this book is gonna be great.

As someone who has been in many toxic and abusive friendships and relationships, to me there is something magic about knowing someone will still be there after a disagreement. Because I've had friendships/relationships where every little disagreement was world-ending.

I did something similar with A Dark and Starless Forest. I wanted the love between Derry and her siblings to be the constant force in her life and the book. They could argue and get mad at each other, but I didn't want their love for each other to ever be a question mark.
Like I'm obsessed with how these kids are going through a LOT, there's just an absurd amount of weird magic murder shit occurring around them, and the constant I want them to have is each other.

There's a lot I love about it but tonight what I love most is the central friendship. I was an adult before I really saw what loving, supportive friendships could look like, and I have a goal to model those in my books so hopefully teens can learn it earlier than I did.
Listen it's only a first draft so right NOW it's not amazing but I genuinely think the book I'm working on now WILL be like.....pretty amazing. I'm really excited about it!!
